profile_positions.description:
As Manager of the International Outsourced Sales Ledger Services Department I was responsible for the day to day operations of a team of 20 Credit and Collections Specialist (inclusive of 2 Supervisors) , managing  the full outsourcing process of  Intrum clients accounts receivables, including invoicing, payment booking, monitoring of due dates, reminder service and above all collection services. 

Key Responsibilities:
•	Definition and implementation of new collection strategies based on the needs of Intrum Justitia clients;
•	Crafting business plans and resource allocation to ensure coverage optimization and scalability;
•	Project manage new client implementations.  This will involve resource planning, documenting of SLA's and process flows, recruitment and training of staff and working closely with the client to ensure all client expectations are managed and delivered within budget and timescales;
•	Together with the Account Manager actively engage with the client to manage and exceed client expectations and cross sell;
•	Support the Sales Director or Managing Director when developing new client opportunities by delivering worked examples of client satisfaction and visions of how an outsourced solution will look;
•	Drive and engage in optimization and scalability project in collaboration with the IT Department;
•	Lead, manage and motivate the team by providing clear expectations, appropriate coaching, mentoring and feedback;
•	HR tasks including training, reviews and internal performance management and employee development;
•	Analyze existing internal operational processes and identify opportunities for improvement
•	Preparing periodic financial reports, needed to deliver reporting on financial performance and operating results.
